<p>Group managers can add entries to their group(s) from this page.</p>
<p>First, select entries by clicking on the box to the left of each entry.  Next, select from the dropdown menu which group to add entries to or remove entries from.  Then, click <b>Add Entry(s)</b> or <b>Remove Entry(s)</b>. The User Group name will appear in the corresponding column below.</p>

<div class="input-group" style="width: 100%;">
  <input type="submit" value="Add" class='form-control' id="add-to-group" style="max-width: 50px;"/>
  <input type="submit" value="Remove" class='form-control' id="remove-from-group" style="max-width: 80px;"/>
  <% groups = Group.joins(:group_users).where(:group_users => {user: current_user, role: "Manager"}) %>
  <% if groups.count > 0 %>  
  <select class='form-control' id="group-select" style="max-width: 200px;">
    <% groups.each do |group| %>
      <option value="<%= group.id %>"><%= group.name %></option>
    <% end %>
  </select>
  <% else %>
  <select name="" id="" class="form-control disabled" style="max-width: 240px" disabled>
    <option value="nil">You have no user groups.</option>
  </select>
  <% end %>
</div>